            <biogHist>
                <p>Ruaraidh or Roderick MacPherson was born to crofting parents John Macpherson and
                    Anne n√©e Ross in Naast, Gairloch in Ross-shire. At the time of the 1881 census,
                    he is found working as a crofter together with his brother Murdoch and his
                    sister Isabella in Poolewe, Gairloch; he is listed as head of the household. All
                    three are described as unmarried. By the time of the 1901 census, Roderick
                    MacPherson is listed as a retired crofter, now with his nephew Duncan Campbell
                    and Campbell's niece Annie. </p>
                <p>He died of 'old age' in April 1910 and his nephew present. It would appear that
                    he never married.</p>
